{
  "tldr": "本文介绍了FORM，一个用于预测细胞形态变化的机器学习框架。通过多通道VQGAN对形态进行编码，并使用扩散模型预测细胞形态变化，支持在不同扰动条件下的形态生成和信号活动预测。", 
  "motivation": "目前计算模型在模拟细胞对外界刺激的反应时受限于二维表示，无法捕捉细胞形态改变的复杂性。因此，FORM的提出是为了构建准确的三维虚拟细胞模型，解决这一瓶颈问题。", 
  "method": "FORM包括一个形态编码器和一个扰动轨迹模块，前者通过多通道VQGAN学习紧凑的3D细胞形态表示，后者则专注于变化的动态轨迹。", 
  "result": "FORM框架已经在一个超过65,000个3D细胞体积的数据集上训练完成，支持无条件的形态生成及条件下的扰动模拟，并可预测信号活动。MorphoEval作为一个评估套件，用于量化扰动引起的形态变化。", 
  "conclusion": "通过结合形态、扰动和功能，FORM和MorphoEval开启了真实3D虚拟细胞模型的制造，在生物医学研究和药物开发中有重要意义。"}
}

{
  "tldr": "PhysWorld is a framework that uses a simulator to create diverse demonstrations for training efficient world models. It includes the construction of a physics-consistent digital twin, perturbation of physical properties, and training of a GNN-based world model. This method improves future predictions for deformable objects and provides faster inference than state-of-the-art methods.",
  "motivation": "The primary motivation is to create physics-consistent dynamics models from limited real-world video data, focusing on deformable objects with spatially-varying physical characteristics, addressing the challenge of sparse data and leading to accurate modeling and prediction of object dynamics.",
  "method": "The method involves constructing a physics-consistent digital twin using the MPM simulator through the selection of a constitutive model, optimizing physical properties from global to local scales, applying part-aware perturbations to the physical properties, and training a lightweight GNN-based world model.",
  "result": "The result is a framework capable of accurate and fast future prediction of deformable object behavior, which generalizes well to novel interactions, significantly outperforming inference speeds over the existing state-of-the-art method (PhysTwin) by 47 times.",
  "conclusion": "PhysWorld demonstrates a competitive performance in terms of both accuracy and speed, creating a foundation that can further refine physical properties through real-world data, providing a significant advancement in interactive world modeling for applications such as robotics, VR, and AR.",
